==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anamorphoscope
<hw>An`a*mor"pho*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Anamorpho</ets>sis + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for restoring a picture or image distorted by anamorphosis to
its normal proportions. It usually consists of a cylindrical
mirror.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anamorphosis</ent>⟦br⟧
